<author>Baz%20Luhrmann</author>
<title>Everybody's%20Free</title>
<date>2000-10-01</date>
<teasertext>Ladies%20and%20gentlemen%20of%20the%20class%20of%20'99%0AWear%20sunscreen.</teasertext>
<content>If%20I%20could%20offer%20you%20only%20one%20tip%20for%20the%20future%2C%20sunscreen%20would%20be%20it%0AA%20long-term%20benefits%20of%20sunscreen%20have%20been%20proved%20by%20scientists%0AWhereas%20the%20rest%20of%20my%20advice%20has%20no%20basis%20more%20reliable%0AThan%20my%20own%20meandering%20experience%2C%20I%20will%20dispense%20this%20advice%20now%0AEnjoy%20the%20power%20and%20beauty%20of%20your%20youth%2C%20oh%2C%20never%20mind%0AYou%20will%20not%20understand%20the%20power%20and%20beauty%20of%20your%20youth%0AUntil%20they've%20faded%2C%20but%20trust%20me%2C%20in%2020%20years%2C%20you'll%20look%20back%0AAt%20photos%20of%20yourself%20and%20recall%20in%20a%20way%20you%20can't%20grasp%20now%0AHow%20much%20possibility%20lay%20before%20you%20and%20how%20fabulous%20you%20really%20looked%0AYou%20are%20not%20as%20fat%20as%20you%20imagine%0ADon't%20worry%20about%20the%20future%0AOr%20worry%2C%20but%20know%20that%20worrying%0AIs%20as%20effective%20as%20trying%20to%20solve%20an%20algebra%20equation%20by%20chewing%20Bubble%20gum%0AThe%20real%20troubles%20in%20your%20life%0AAre%20apt%20to%20be%20things%20that%20never%20crossed%20your%20worried%20mind%0AThe%20kind%20that%20blindsides%20you%20at%204%20p.m.%20on%20some%20idle%20Tuesday%0ADo%20one%20thing%20every%20day%20that%20scares%20you%0ASaying%2C%20don't%20be%20reckless%20with%20other%20people's%20hearts%0ADon't%20put%20up%20with%20people%20who%20are%20reckless%20with%20yours%0AFloss%0ADon't%20waste%20your%20time%20on%20jealousy%0ASometimes%20you're%20ahead%2C%20sometimes%20you're%20behind%0AThe%20race%20is%20long%20and%20in%20the%20end%2C%20it's%20only%20with%20yourself%0ARemember%20compliments%20you%20receive%2C%20forget%20the%20insults%0AIf%20you%20succeed%20in%20doing%20this%2C%20tell%20me%20how%0AKeep%20your%20old%20love%20letters%2C%20throw%20away%20your%20old%20bank%20statements%0AStretch%0ADon't%20feel%20guilty%20if%20you%20don't%20know%20what%20you%20want%20to%20do%20with%20your%20life%0AThe%20most%20interesting%20people%20I%20know%0ADidn't%20know%20at%2022%20what%20they%20wanted%20to%20do%20with%20their%20lives%0ASome%20of%20the%20most%20interesting%2040-year-olds%20I%20know%20still%20don't%0AGet%20plenty%20of%20calcium%0ABe%20kind%20to%20your%20knees%0AYou'll%20miss%20them%20when%20they're%20gone%0AMaybe%20you'll%20marry%2C%20maybe%20you%20won't%0AMaybe%20you'll%20have%20children%2C%20maybe%20you%20won't%0AMaybe%20you'll%20divorce%20at%2040%2C%20maybe%20you'll%20dance%20the%20'Funky%20Chicken'%0AOn%20your%2075th%20wedding%20anniversary%0AWhatever%20you%20do%2C%20don't%20congratulate%20yourself%20too%20much%0AOr%20berate%20yourself%20either%0AYour%20choices%20are%20half%20chance%2C%20so%20are%20everybody%20else's%0AEnjoy%20your%20body%2C%20use%20it%20every%20way%20you%20can%0ADon't%20be%20afraid%20of%20it%20or%20what%20other%20people%20think%20of%20it%0AIt's%20the%20greatest%20instrument%20you'll%20ever%20own%0ADance%2C%20even%20if%20you%20have%20nowhere%20to%20do%20it%20but%20your%20own%20living%20room%0ARead%20the%20directions%20even%20if%20you%20don't%20follow%20them%0ADo%20not%20read%20beauty%20magazines%2C%20they%20will%20only%20make%20you%20feel%20ugly%0AGet%20to%20know%20your%20parents%2C%20you%20never%20know%20when%20they'll%20be%20gone%20for%20good%0ABe%20nice%20to%20your%20siblings%2C%20they're%20your%20best%20link%20to%20your%20past%0AAnd%20the%20people%20most%20likely%20to%20stick%20with%20you%20in%20the%20future%0AUnderstand%20that%20friends%20come%20and%20go%0ABut%20a%20precious%20few%2C%20who%20should%20hold%20on%0AWork%20hard%20to%20bridge%20the%20gaps%20in%20geography%20and%20lifestyle%0AFor%20as%20the%20older%20you%20get%0AThe%20more%20you%20need%20the%20people%20you%20knew%20when%20you%20were%20young%0ALive%20in%20New%20York%20City%20once%20but%20leave%20before%20it%20makes%20you%20hard%0ALive%20in%20northern%20California%20once%20but%20leave%20before%20it%20makes%20you%20soft%0ATravel%0AAccept%20certain%20inalienable%20truths%0APrices%20will%20rise%2C%20politicians%20will%20philander%2C%20you%20too%2C%20will%20get%20old%0AAnd%20when%20you%20do%2C%20you'll%20fantasize%20that%20when%20you%20were%20young%0APrices%20were%20reasonable%2C%20politicians%20were%20noble%0AAnd%20children%20respected%20their%20elders%0ARespect%20your%20elders%0ADon't%20expect%20anyone%20else%20to%20support%20you%0AMaybe%20you%20have%20a%20trust%20fund%2C%20maybe%20you'll%20have%20a%20wealthy%20spouse%0ABut%20you%20never%20know%20when%20either%20one%20might%20run%20out%0ADon't%20mess%20too%20much%20with%20your%20hair%0AOr%20by%20the%20time%20you're%2040%20it%20will%20look%2085%0ABe%20careful%20whose%20advice%20you%20buy%20but%20be%20patient%20with%20those%20who%20supply%20it%0AAdvice%20is%20a%20form%20of%20nostalgia%2C%20dispensing%20it%20is%20a%20way%20of%20fishing%20the%20past%0AFrom%20the%20disposal%2C%20wiping%20it%20off%2C%20painting%20over%20the%20ugly%20parts%0AAnd%20recycling%20it%20for%20more%20than%20it's%20worth%0ABut%20trust%20me%20on%20the%20sunscreen.</content>
